== Generating documentation for Rails

If you want to generate documentation for Rails itself, there is a handy trick. Railsâ€™ RDoc tasks obey the <tt>template</tt> environment variable. For instance, to document ActiveRecord with Allison, run:

  cd vendor/rails/activerecord/
  template='/path/to/allison/allison' rake rerdoc

The template value should be the full path to the <tt>allison.rb</tt> file, minus the <tt>.rb</tt> (contrary to the Rake task).

